			<section>
									<div class="summary">
						<p>Enables magic finders. These provide some syntactic-sugar which allows
to i.e. use <code>Model::all()</code> instead  of <code>Model::find('all')</code>.</p>
					</div>
				
									<div class="description">
						<pre><code class="language-php">// Retrieves post with id `23` using the `'first'` finder.
Posts::first(['conditions' =&gt; ['id' =&gt; 23]]);
Posts::findById(23);
Posts::findById(23);

// All posts that have a trueish `is_published` field.
Posts::all(['conditions' =&gt; ['is_published' =&gt; true]]);
Posts::findAll(['conditions' =&gt; ['is_published' =&gt; true]]);
Posts::findAllByIsPublshed(true)

// Counts all posts.
Posts::count()
</code></pre>
					</div>
